						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of Durgā-Paramēśvarī temple.</p>						

						<p>Ballamahādēvī.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record registers a gift of money, the details of which are all lost. It refers to the queen as ruling from <hi rend="bold">Bārahakanyāpura</hi> and mentions <hi rend="italic">kumāra</hi> Pāṇḍyadēvarasa. The queen is eulogised in the beginning.</p>						

						</summary>
